^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Okay, a couple of things about this hand. Over 1S, Eddy could bid 1N, but he is definitely marginal at best. So, pass is ok  and I have a clear pass. Now, there is a cardinal rule in balancing seat. If the opponents open 1 of a major and it goes P-P you are just about required to balance. The only exception is if you have a bad hand (< 10) and length in their suit. Since Kerrie is short in spades, she has to balance. If she bids 2D, things work out great for her side, as they have a 9 card diamond fit. |
