^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|The reasoning for the auction works thusly. West is sure East has a singleton or void somewhere (since East is 5-5 in the majors, mathematically she must have a singleton or void). 5D says West has the diamond Ace but is worried about clubs. East, with a club singleton, can bid 5H, which shows the heart Ace and a club control. (without club control East must bid 5S, because she knows that they have 2 club losers, East having denied a club control). Once East shows the club control, West has an easy 6S bid. |
