{^*BBidding Objectives^*N}

Auctions have only 2 simple objectives:
1. Bid game or slam if possible, otherwise stay as low as you can.
2. Find a good strain (trump suit or NT).|
PG| ***** 199 ***** |


AT|

Marty Bergen says, "If one of those objectives can be resolved quickly, you are then free to concentrate on resolving the other one." Then he continues,|
PG| ***** 200 ***** |


AT|

"In "|CP|8|at|standard|CP||AT|," Jacoby 2NT is "on" only when:

^c1.  partner opens 1H or 1S in first or second seat;
^c2.  your RHO passes.

When you respond by jumping to 2NT, your bid is alertable. The bid promises:
^Ca.  4+ trumps (not 3);
^cb.  13+ dummy points, with no upper limit. 

Remember: When we have a fit, "points" does NOT refer to HCP only. In addition to sensible evaluating, including Adjust-3, responder must be adding points for short suits." |
